pageContext.description: Part of blade missing; the fractured face is thinly patinated, with traces of bronze-colour showing. Single rib extends down face of blade (about 1") on each side below stopridge.
pageContext.surface: Very rough and pitted.Green patina. Traces of browny black colour of clay-colour, and of white.
pageContext.collection: Miss. N. E. Reed. 18 Woodlands Road, Southall, Middlesex (July, 1938)
pageContext.site: England, greater london,southall (near),found in 1900, making the canal between southall and slough (in the middlesex part of it) not far from southall. precise locality unknown.
